{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":19837,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2017-08-03T22:13:51.202Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôd like to introduce support of sparse navigation meshes with dynamically streamed tiles.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUrho3D branch with this feature and two samples is available here:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/eugeneko/Urho3D/tree/navmesh-streaming\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://github.com/eugeneko/Urho3D/tree/navmesh-streaming\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt‚Äôs a kind of sketch, so I would be happy if someone test and/or review it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/1X/d68f9da197ddf7b3d1bd065114c648e66b166a16.jpg\" title=\"49_CrowdNavigationStreaming_d 2017-08-04 01-06-50-290.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/1X/d68f9da197ddf7b3d1bd065114c648e66b166a16_2_666x500.jpg\" alt=\"49_CrowdNavigationStreaming_d 2017-08-04 01-06-50-290\" width=\"666\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/1X/d68f9da197ddf7b3d1bd065114c648e66b166a16_2_666x500.jpg, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/1X/d68f9da197ddf7b3d1bd065114c648e66b166a16_2_999x750.jpg 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/1X/d68f9da197ddf7b3d1bd065114c648e66b166a16.jpg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/1X/d68f9da197ddf7b3d1bd065114c648e66b166a16_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003e49_CrowdNavigationStreaming_d 2017-08-04 01-06-50-290.jpg\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1024√ó768 684 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eGuide\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFirst of all, \u003ccode\u003eNavigationMesh::Allocate()\u003c/code\u003e shall be used instead of \u003ccode\u003eNavigationMesh::Build()\u003c/code\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003enavMesh-\u0026gt;Allocate(boundingBox, maxTiles);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe bounding box of the entire area is almost unlimited (I hope), but it shall be somehow computed on the user side. Then, user shall provide the limit for simultaneously loaded mesh tiles.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThen, navigation mesh shall be built. It is actually fine to use \u003ccode\u003eNavigationMesh::Build()\u003c/code\u003e first time and \u003ccode\u003eNavigationMesh::Allocate()\u003c/code\u003e other times, but huge areas may cause \u003ccode\u003eout of memory\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eNavigationMesh::Build(fromTile, toTile)\u003c/code\u003e could be used to build few tiles in the rectangular area specified.\u003cbr\u003e\nThen, these tiles could be received via \u003ccode\u003eNavigationMesh::GetTileData(x, z)\u003c/code\u003e and e.g. saved onto disk.\u003cbr\u003e\nTo build next bucket of tiles, do \u003ccode\u003eNavigationMesh::RemoveAllTiles()\u003c/code\u003e first.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe simplest example:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003efor each tile\n{\n    navMesh-\u0026gt;Build(tile, tile);\n    tileData = navMesh-\u0026gt;GetTileData(tile.x, tile.y);\n    SaveToDisk(tileData);\n    navMesh-\u0026gt;RemoveAllTiles();\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eStored tiles could be added to and removed from navigation mesh via \u003ccode\u003eNavigationMesh::AddTile(tileData)\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eNavigationMesh::RemoveTile(x, z)\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eKnown issues\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cs\u003e\u003ccode\u003eObstacle\u003c/code\u003es shall be re-added on the user side once \u003ccode\u003eAddTile\u003c/code\u003e is called in order to be correctly rendered into navigation mesh.\u003c/s\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cs\u003e\u003ccode\u003eCrowdAgent\u003c/code\u003es linked to removed chunks become invalid and stuck. This shall be handled somehow at the user side.\u003c/s\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cs\u003e\u003ccode\u003eOffMeshConnection\u003c/code\u003e sometimes doesn‚Äôt work properly.\u003c/s\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ccode\u003eOffMeshConnection\u003c/code\u003e sometimes doesn‚Äôt work properly even without streaming.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eCrowdAgent\u003c/code\u003e may behave strangely if its path lays through removed tile.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAny streaming logic shall be implemented on the user side.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-05-23T13:20:01.554Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":336,"reads":69,"readers_count":68,"score":1873.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":3416,"topic_slug":"streaming-of-navigation-meshes","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":4,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/eugeneko/Urho3D/tree/navmesh-streaming","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"eugeneko/Urho3D","clicks":52},{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/1X/d68f9da197ddf7b3d1bd065114c648e66b166a16.jpg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"d68f9da197ddf7b3d1bd065114c648e66b166a16.jpg","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":6}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":19840,"name":"","username":"slapin","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/dfb087/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-08-04T07:00:56.738Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eAh, this is so cool!\u003cbr\u003e\nHow do you display this debug geometry?\u003cbr\u003e\nAlso would you like to handle obstacles and agents in a way so it would be more transparent\u003cbr\u003e\n(or more or less clear what to do about them)?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-08-04T07:00:56.738Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":55,"readers_count":54,"score":16.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":3416,"topic_slug":"streaming-of-navigation-meshes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":554,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":19841,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2017-08-04T07:45:24.348Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eDidn‚Äôt look in any detail, but concept is very cool!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-08-04T07:45:24.348Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":56,"readers_count":55,"score":11.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":3416,"topic_slug":"streaming-of-navigation-meshes","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":19843,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2017-08-04T08:19:03.476Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"slapin\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"3416\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/dfb087/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e slapin:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHow do you display this debug geometry?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI draw all tiles currently added to the navmesh.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"slapin\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"3416\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/dfb087/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e slapin:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAlso would you like to handle obstacles and agents in a way so it would be more transparent\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e(or more or less clear what to do about them)?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOh, I definently would like to do something. I just don‚Äôt know what.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ccode\u003e49_CrowdNavigationStreaming\u003c/code\u003e contains workaround for these issues, but it‚Äôs not the best way of doing things‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMy changes now has zero cost: user don‚Äôt pay for streaming neither CPU nor memory if he doesn‚Äôt use it. I don‚Äôt know how to keep zero cost and fix the issues simultaneously.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHuh‚Ä¶ I can send some event from the navmesh and somehow handle it in \u003ccode\u003eCrowdAgent\u003c/code\u003es and \u003ccode\u003eObstacle\u003c/code\u003es‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-08-04T08:34:34.005Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":54,"readers_count":53,"score":10.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":3416,"topic_slug":"streaming-of-navigation-meshes","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":19852,"name":"","username":"Mike","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/58f4c7/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-08-04T11:56:47.023Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWorks great \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/grinning.png?v=5\" title=\":grinning:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":grinning:\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nJust noticed that the character doesn‚Äôt move with a 9 tiles grid (streamingDistance_ set to 1).\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-08-04T11:56:47.023Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":46,"readers_count":45,"score":9.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":3416,"topic_slug":"streaming-of-navigation-meshes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Contributor","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":9,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":19878,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2017-08-04T19:43:41.450Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI fixed the problem with Obstacles. They are automatically re-added if \u003ccode\u003eAddTile\u003c/code\u003e was called for the tile intersected with the obstacle. \u003ccode\u003eCrowdAgent\u003c/code\u003es are harder to handle‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-08-04T19:43:41.450Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":44,"readers_count":43,"score":53.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":3416,"topic_slug":"streaming-of-navigation-meshes","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":19879,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2017-08-04T20:33:17.634Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI fixed \u003ccode\u003eCrowdAgent\u003c/code\u003es. They still just stuck when become out-of-mesh, but they are re-added (and so repaired) once the underlying tile is added to the navigation mesh. IMO this is enough.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/cadaver\"\u003e@cadaver\u003c/a\u003e I found some strange logic in navmesh transform calculations‚Ä¶ Does navmesh really support node transform or not? E.g. look at NavigationMesh::CollectGeometries.\u003cbr\u003e\nNavigationGeometryInfo bounding boxes for geometry are stored in the node space‚Ä¶\u003cbr\u003e\nBut right below the boxes for NavArea and OffMeshConnection are stored in the world space o_o\u003cbr\u003e\nObstacles are also added to the mesh in the world space.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-08-04T20:33:28.724Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":45,"readers_count":44,"score":89.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":3416,"topic_slug":"streaming-of-navigation-meshes","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core dev